 begin tonight, as each team selects two athletes to represent them at the Parade of Nations, taking place along the River Seine.\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Basketball legend James, who won gold at the London Olympics in 2012, will be accompanied by tennis star Gauff, who makes her Olympic debut in Paris.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_the_Great\", \"score\": 0.9999914128152696, \"rank\": 8.587238091571506e-06, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_the_Great\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_the_Great\"}, {\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 896, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.477761232690414e-109, \"text\": \"London Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 979, \"end\": 984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.86794096996923e-49, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both of America's brightest athletes will be the penultimate pair to carry their country's flag at the parade, behind host nation France's Florent Manaudou and Melina Robert-Michon.\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1116, \"end\": 1122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 1.0, 